    <!-- Add Activity -->

    <activity>
        <introduction>
            <p>
                <alert>Work in Groups</alert>
            </p>
            <p>
                
            </p>
            <p>
                <alert>What you need</alert>
            </p>
            <p>
                In groups, choose <m>4</m> members and assigned each of them the following roles:
            </p>
            <p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Person 1: Chooses a number
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Person 2: Adds
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Person 3: Multiplies
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Person 4 : The Announcer
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p>
                The group will work together to find the secret number chosen by Person 1 (value of <m>x</m>).
            </p>
            <p>
                <alert>What to do</alert>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Person <m>1</m> chooses a single-digit number <m>x</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Constraint: <m>x≤5</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            They whisper it to Person <m>2</m> only
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Person <m>2</m> adds <m>5</m> to the secret number (<m>x + 5</m>). 
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Person <m>2</m> and Person <m>1</m> both whisper their numbers to Person <m>3</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Person <m>3</m> multiplies [<m>x \times (x + 5)</m>] and whispers the result to Person <m>4</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Person <m>4</m> announces the final result.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>

        </introduction>
        <task>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    If person <m>4</m> says the product is <m>14</m>, can you guess the secret number?
                </p>
            </statement>
        </task>
        <task>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    What if person <m>4</m> says the product is <m>13.5</m>?
                </p>
                <p>
                    Is it possible to guess the secret number? Why or why not?
                </p>
                <p>
                    How will you find the secret number in this case? Give the value of <m>x</m> that satisfies the equation.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </task>
        <task>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Repeat the activity with person <m>2</m> using a different number and person <m>4</m> should announce a different product result.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </task>
        <task>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    What method did you use to solve the equations?
                </p>
                <p>
                    What are the advantages of using the quadratic formula compared to other methods of solving quadratic equations?
                </p>
                <p>
                    Can you think of any real-life situations where applying the quadratic formula would be useful?
                </p>
            </statement>
        </task>
        <task>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Share your work with the other learners in the class.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </task>
    </activity> 

